column3: Monthly catch of tuna, tuna-like and shark species in the Atlantic Ocean (%year_start%-%year_end%) aggregated by 5° squares (IRD level 0)
column13: This dataset lists catch of tuna, tuna-like and shark species in the Atlantic Ocean from %year_start% to %year_end%. Catches are stratified by year, month, species, gear, vessel flag reporting country, fishing mode (i.e. type of school used), area (mainly 5° square resolution) and unit of catch (weight or number). This dataset was generated using public domain datasets released by the International Commission for the Conservation of Atlantic Tunas (ICCAT). IRD Level 0 stands for the processes applied to the primary datasets by the French National Research Institute for Sustainable Development (IRD) to generate the dataset. Data are expressed using ICCAT's coding system.

column3: Monthly catch of tuna, tuna-like and shark species (%year_start%-%year_end%) by purse seiners and pole-and-liners in the Indian, Atlantic and Eastern Pacific Oceans aggregated by 1° squares (IRD level 0)
column13: This dataset lists catch of tuna, tuna-like and shark species by purse seiners and pole-and-liners from %year_start% to %year_end% in the Indian, Atlantic and Eastern Pacific Oceans. Catches are stratified by month, species, gear, vessel flag reporting country, fishing mode (i.e. type of school used), area (mainly 1° square) and unit of catch (weight or number). This dataset was computed using public domain catch-and-effort datasets released by four of the five tuna Regional Fisheries Management Organizations: the Indian Ocean Tuna Commission (IOTC), the International Commission for the Conservation of Atlantic Tunas (ICCAT), the Inter-American Tropical Tuna Commission (IATTC), the Commission for the Conservation of Southern Bluefin Tuna (CCSBT). Data from the Western Pacific Ocean were not included because WCPFC provides purse seine and pole-and-line catch at 5° square spatial resolution. IRD Level 0 stands for the processes applied to the primary datasets by the French National Research Institute for Sustainable Development (IRD) to generate the dataset.
